wn" data-v-b3358103=""><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">The user wants me to build a complete live web app based on the Xbox VR Dashboard blueprint they've been working on. Looking at the uploaded files, I can see:</div><ol start="1"><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A PDF document with extensive blueprint documentation for an Xbox VR Dashboard</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Several images including:</div><ul start="1"><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A MediaCodec test plan</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A cardboard VR headset stencil/blueprint</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A cardboard VR headset assembled with a phone</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A development roadmap</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A component architecture table</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A concept art of the VR dashboard</div></li></ul></li></ol><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">The blueprint describes:</div><ul start="1"><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A VR dashboard using A-Frame (WebXR)</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Xbox Remote Play integration via Better xCloud</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Spatial multitasking with multiple virtual screens</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Bluetooth controller support</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Barrel distortion shader for lens correction</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Manual focus/zoom controls</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Android background service for persistence</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A cardboard VR headset design</div></li></ul><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">The user wants a "complete live web app" - since I can only generate downloadable files via ipython (charts/data), but I can create an interactive HTML web app that demonstrates the VR dashboard concept. Given the constraints, I should build a fully functional, interactive HTML file that:</div><ol start="1"><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Uses A-Frame for the 3D VR environment</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Has a curved main screen for Xbox gaming</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Has side panels for browser/apps</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Includes the barrel distortion shader</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Has controller input simulation (since we can't access real Bluetooth controllers in a web app easily, but we can simulate with keyboard)</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Has a cyberpunk/dark theme matching the concept art</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Is a single self-contained HTML file that can run in a browser</div></li></ol><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Since this is a web app that will be model-generated, I need to save it to <!--[--><code class="segment-code-inline" data-v-e8232542="">/mnt/agents/output/</code><!--]--> and provide a download link.</div><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Let me create a comprehensive, interactive HTML file that brings the blueprint to life. I'll include:</div><ul start="1"><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A-Frame scene with the spatial layout</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Custom barrel distortion shader</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Keyboard/controller input handling for zoom</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Simulated Xbox dashboard UI on the main screen</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Side panels for browser and system stats</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Animated elements</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">A loading screen</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Responsive design</div></li></ul><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Actually, looking more carefully at the images and PDF, the concept art (1000945710.jpg) shows a very specific aesthetic - dark, cyberpunk, neon green accents, with a central curved screen showing a space game, left side browser, right side social chat and system stats.</div><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Let me build this as a single, comprehensive HTML file with embedded CSS and JavaScript. I'll use A-Frame from CDN and create a rich interactive experience.</div><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Key features to implement:</div><ol start="1"><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>3D VR Environment</strong>: A-Frame scene with dark environment</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Central Curved Screen</strong>: Large curved display showing Xbox/game content (I'll use a canvas texture with animated space scene to simulate gameplay)</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Left Screen</strong>: Browser window with simulated web content</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Right Screens</strong>: Social chat and system monitoring panels</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Bottom Dock</strong>: Quick access controls</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Barrel Distortion Shader</strong>: Custom GLSL shader for lens correction with zoom uniform</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Input Handling</strong>: Keyboard controls (arrow keys) for zoom/focus, WASD for looking around</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Controller Simulation</strong>: Visual representation of controller input</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Performance HUD</strong>: FPS and latency display</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Loading/Intro</strong>: A cinematic entry</div></li></ol><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Since this needs to be a "live web app", I'll make it as polished and interactive as possible within a single HTML file.</div><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Let me write the code using ipython to save the file.</div></div></div><!--]--></div></div> <!----></div></div><!--]--><!--]--></div><div class="block-item" data-v-e2ab115e=""><!--[--><div data-v-18a6bdcd=""><div class="toolcall-container default toolcall-ipython" data-v-18a6bdcd="" data-v-9606ddcc=""><div class="toolcall-title-container default" data-v-9606ddcc="" data-v-bc9c95fe=""><div class="line toolcall-title-name" data-v-bc9c95fe=""><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" role="img" class="iconify toolcall-title-name-icon" style="" width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 1024 1024" name="Code" data-v-bc9c95fe=""><path d="M705.28 642.56a35.541333 35.541333 0 0 1 0 70.741333l-3.669333 0.170667H512a35.541333 35.541333 0 0 1 0-71.082667h189.610667l3.626666 0.170667zM297.216 320.938667a35.584 35.584 0 0 1 47.573333-2.432l2.730667 2.432 114.261333 114.261333a75.093333 75.093333 0 0 1 0 106.197333l-114.261333 114.261334-2.730667 2.474666a35.584 35.584 0 0 1-50.005333-50.048l2.432-2.730666 114.304-114.261334a3.968 3.968 0 0 0 0-5.589333L297.173333 371.2a35.584 35.584 0 0 1 0-50.261333z" fill="currentColor"></path><path d="M725.333333 132.266667A166.4 166.4 0 0 1 891.733333 298.666667v426.666666a166.4 166.4 0 0 1-166.4 166.4H298.666667A166.4 166.4 0 0 1 132.266667 725.333333V298.666667A166.4 166.4 0 0 1 298.666667 132.266667h426.666666zM298.666667 209.066667A89.6 89.6 0 0 0 209.066667 298.666667v426.666666c0 49.493333 40.106667 89.6 89.6 89.6h426.666666a89.6 89.6 0 0 0 89.6-89.6V298.666667A89.6 89.6 0 0 0 725.333333 209.066667H298.666667z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg> <span class="toolcall-title-name-text" data-v-bc9c95fe="">Execute Python code</span></div> <!----> <div class="toolcall-title-container-extra" data-v-bc9c95fe=""><!--[--><!--]--> <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" role="img" class="iconify toolcall-title-container-extra-arrow" style="" width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 1024 1024" name="Right_b" data-v-bc9c95fe=""><path 